{{Politics of Guinea}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Guinea]] on 11 November 2001. The new constitution would remove presidential term limits, and increase the term from five to seven years.<ref name=AED>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/gn.html Elections in Guinea] African Elections Database</ref> It was approved by 98.36% of voters, and although boycotted by the opposition,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/1032515.stm Guinea Timeline] BBC News</ref> turnout was reported to be 87.2% turnout.<ref name=AED/>
